<subSubSection id="66C5058FFFC4FF930790FAF011D7898E" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC4FF930790FAF012C68977" blockId="25.[143,1103,1286,1508]" box="[143,251,1286,1309]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">
<heading id="7528E168FFC4FF930790FAF012C68977" box="[143,251,1286,1309]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC4FF930790FAF012C68977" box="[143,251,1286,1309]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC4FF930790FADB11D7898E" blockId="25.[143,1103,1286,1508]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">
Females of this new species bear very close resemblance to those of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC4FF9304A4FAD81284890F" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sesieutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC4FF9304A4FAD81284890F" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">J. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC4FF9307DAFABA1378890E" box="[197,325,1356,1380]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having large, medially situated copulatory orifices, and similar shape of spermathecae. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC4FF93052AFA9B108489EE" authority="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop, 2013" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" box="[565,697,1389,1412]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoonae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC4FF93052AFA9B108489EE" box="[565,697,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">J. angoonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC4FF9305DDFA9B112489EE" box="[706,793,1389,1412]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the copulatory orifices are teardrop-shaped (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC4FF93064AFA7A13FB89CE" box="[341,454,1420,1444]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="13.[143,210,790,812]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,169,757]" captionTargetId="figure-5@13.[145,1102,169,758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 7. Jacaena spp. Epigynal region, ventral (A–F). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (A); J. punctata sp. nov., paratype (B); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (C); J. mihun (D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517662/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Figure 7E</figureCitation>
) and the insemination ducts are tubular without any modification (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC4FF9307E7FA5A135789AE" box="[248,362,1452,1476]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Figure 8E</figureCitation>
) whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC4FF9306EBFA5B109989AE" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[500,676,1452,1476]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sesieutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC4FF9306EBFA5B109989AE" box="[500,676,1452,1476]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">J. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC4FF9305B4FA5A111989AE" box="[683,804,1452,1476]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the orifices are subcircular (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC4FF930788FA3A1336898E" box="[151,267,1484,1508]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="13.[143,210,790,812]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,169,757]" captionTargetId="figure-5@13.[145,1102,169,758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 7. Jacaena spp. Epigynal region, ventral (A–F). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (A); J. punctata sp. nov., paratype (B); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (C); J. mihun (D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517662/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Figure 7A</figureCitation>
) and the median part of the ducts is greatly enlarged (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC4FF930476FA3A11E1898E" box="[873,988,1484,1508]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Figure 8F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66C5058FFFC4FF930790F9CC10D18AF0" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC4FF930790F9CC133A8A38" blockId="25.[143,1103,1594,1690]" box="[143,263,1594,1618]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">
<heading id="7528E168FFC4FF930790F9CC133A8A38" box="[143,263,1594,1618]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC4FF930790F9CC133A8A38" box="[143,263,1594,1618]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC4FF930790F99410D18AF0" blockId="25.[143,1103,1594,1690]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1562">The specific epithet is an eponymous patronym (genitive form of a noun) dedicated to Dr Angoon Lewvanich, a prolific Thai taxonomist.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="7AA0068CFFC7FF9007CCFBD213EF881E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517678" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6517678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517678/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" startId="26.[211,278,1060,1082]" targetBox="[213,1167,169,1027]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC7FF9007CCFBD213EF881E" blockId="26.[211,1172,1060,1140]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">
Figure 14. 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC7FF900657FBD313C18850" authority="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop, 2013" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" box="[328,508,1061,1082]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoonae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC7FF900657FBD313C18850" box="[328,508,1061,1082]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">Jacaena angoonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC7FF90051CFBD2106E8853" box="[515,595,1060,1081]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, female (A–C); 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC7FF900443FBD311EE8850" authority="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop, 2013" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" box="[860,979,1060,1082]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC7FF900443FBD311EE8850" box="[860,979,1060,1082]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">J. peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC7FF9004C5FBD216178853" box="[986,1066,1060,1081]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, female (D, E). Epigyne, ventral (A, D). Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (B, E). Proximal part of insemination duct (C).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="66C5058FFFC7FF9607CCFB4A130E8D4D" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="1565" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" type="description">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC7FF9007CCFB4A136F88B9" blockId="26.[211,1172,1212,1691]" box="[211,338,1212,1235]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">
<heading id="7528E168FFC7FF9007CCFB4A136F88B9" box="[211,338,1212,1235]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC7FF9007CCFB4A136F88B9" box="[211,338,1212,1235]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC7FF9007CCFB12119189B0" blockId="26.[211,1172,1212,1691]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC7FF9007CCFB12131F8896" box="[211,290,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="F164E8A6FFC7FF900626FB15139F8891" box="[313,418,1251,1275]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length 7.5. Carapace 3.0 long, 2.4 wide. Opisthosoma 4.5 long, 2.6 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.10; ALE 0.13; PME 0.08; PLE 0.11; AME–AME 0.06; AME–ALE 0.05; PME–PME 0.13; PME–PLE 0.16. MOQ 0.36 long; front width 0.28; back width 0.33. Leg formula 4123. Spination. Leg I: femur 1–1pl; tibia 8pl 8rl; metatarsus 4pl 4rl. Leg II: tibia 7pl 6rl; metatarsus 4pl 4rl. Leg III: tibia 1–1–1v 1pl; metatarsus 1–1v 1pl. Leg IV: tibia 1–1–1–1–2v 1–1rl; metatarsus 1–1– 1v 1pl 1rl. Leg measurements: Leg I 8.6 (2.5, 1.0, 2.3, 1.85, 1.0); II 7.7 (2.2, 0.9, 1.9, 1.7, 1.0); III 6.1 (1.7, 0.8, 1.4, 0.85); IV 9.2 (2.5, 1.0, 2.1, 2.4, 1.2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC7FF9007E1FA14105E8AF0" blockId="26.[211,1172,1212,1691]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">
Colouration and pattern (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC7FF900500FA1410A58990" box="[543,664,1506,1530]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[211,278,1132,1154]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1099]" captionTargetId="figure-5@6.[213,1170,168,1099]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Females of Jacaena spp., habitus, dorsal (A–H). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (A); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratypes (B, C); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (D); J. punctata sp. nov., paratypes (E,F); J. mihun (G); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype (H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517642/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1563">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
): Carapace dark chestnut-brown; integument coarsely granulated. Chelicerae, sternum, labium and gnathocoxae dark reddishbrown; coxae, trochanters and femora dark brown; patellae and tibiae brown, tibiae orange distally; metatarsi and tarsi I–II light brown, III–IV orange. Opisthosoma ovoid; dorsum with pattern consisting of paired, oblique patches, followed by three chevrons on dark grey background.
</paragraph>
<caption id="7AA0068CFFC6FF910790FAEF11E58926" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517680" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6517680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517680/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564" startId="27.[143,210,1305,1327]" targetBox="[145,1102,169,1272]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC6FF910790FAEF11E58926" blockId="27.[143,1104,1305,1356]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">
Figure 15. 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC6FF91061BFAEC138D8945" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1897" box="[260,432,1305,1327]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC6FF91061BFAEC138D8945" box="[260,432,1305,1327]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Jacaena distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, female (MSNG). Museum label (A). Original label by Thorell (B). Habitus, dorsal (C). Ditto, ventral (D). Epigyne, partially removed (E).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC6FF9107A5FA7513EF8A30" blockId="27.[143,1104,1411,1626]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">
Copulatory organ (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF91068BFA75102E89F1" box="[404,531,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="13.[143,210,790,812]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,169,757]" captionTargetId="figure-5@13.[145,1102,169,758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 7. Jacaena spp. Epigynal region, ventral (A–F). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (A); J. punctata sp. nov., paratype (B); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (C); J. mihun (D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517662/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Figures 7E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF91053FFA75107C89F1" box="[544,577,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">8E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF910551FA75109F89F1" box="[590,674,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="26.[211,278,1060,1082]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,169,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-5@26.[213,1170,169,1027]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figure 14. Jacaena angoonae sp. nov., holotype, female (A–C); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype, female (D, E). Epigyne, ventral (A, D). Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (B, E). Proximal part of insemination duct (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517678/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">14A–C</figureCitation>
): Copulatory orifices teardrop-shaped (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF910788FA55131C89D1" box="[151,289,1443,1467]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="26.[211,278,1060,1082]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,169,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-5@26.[213,1170,169,1027]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figure 14. Jacaena angoonae sp. nov., holotype, female (A–C); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype, female (D, E). Epigyne, ventral (A, D). Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (B, E). Proximal part of insemination duct (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517678/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Figure 14A</figureCitation>
). Insemination ducts elongated, loosely coiled (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF910453FA5511EE89D1" box="[844,979,1443,1467]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="26.[211,278,1060,1082]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,169,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-5@26.[213,1170,169,1027]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figure 14. Jacaena angoonae sp. nov., holotype, female (A–C); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype, female (D, E). Epigyne, ventral (A, D). Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (B, E). Proximal part of insemination duct (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517678/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Figure 14B</figureCitation>
); proximal duct connected to copulatory orifice semi-transparent (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF910419FA34114189B0" box="[774,892,1474,1498]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Figure 8E</figureCitation>
), forming sigmoid arch; secretory ampullae situated on posterior surface of proximal ducts; distal half of duct ascending anteriorly then descending posteriorly to connect with spermathecae. Spermathecae elliptical, anterior part distinctly enlarged, more or less spherical with glandular pore (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFC6FF91065CF9B413FB8A30" box="[323,454,1602,1626]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="26.[211,278,1060,1082]" captionTargetBox="[213,1167,169,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-5@26.[213,1170,169,1027]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figure 14. Jacaena angoonae sp. nov., holotype, female (A–C); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype, female (D, E). Epigyne, ventral (A, D). Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (B, E). Proximal part of insemination duct (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517678/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Figure 14B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC6FF910790F974136C8AF0" blockId="27.[143,337,1666,1690]" box="[143,337,1666,1690]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">
<heading id="7528E168FFC6FF910790F974136C8AF0" box="[143,337,1666,1690]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC6FF910790F97412F48AF0" box="[143,201,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1564">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC1FF9607CCFF5E13418CAA" blockId="28.[211,1172,168,295]" box="[211,380,168,192]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565">
<heading id="7528E168FFC1FF9607CCFF5E13418CAA" box="[211,380,168,192]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC1FF9607CCFF5E13418CAA" box="[211,380,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565">Natural history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFC1FF9607CCFF26130E8D4D" blockId="28.[211,1172,168,295]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565">
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC1FF9607CCFF26139D8C8D" authority="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop, 2013" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" box="[211,416,208,231]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoonae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC1FF9607CCFF26139D8C8D" box="[211,416,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565">Jacaena angoonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFC1FF9606B2FF26103A8C8D" box="[429,519,208,231]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
inhabits evergreen hill forest of Doi Chang (
<quantity id="E927FBE1FFC1FF960335FF3916BA8C8D" box="[1066,1159,207,231]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.93" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565" unit="m" value="1930.0">1930 m</quantity>
). This new species marks the highest altitudinal record among members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFC1FF9607CCFEE613168D4D" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1897" box="[211,299,272,295]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFC1FF9607CCFEE613168D4D" box="[211,299,272,295]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1565">Jacaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
